&lt;p&gt;The government unveiled the Pakistan Economic Survey (PES) for FY2025-26 on Thursday, according to which GDP growth was recorded at 3.7pc in the outgoing fiscal year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This  is higher than last year’s growth of 3.18pc but falls short of its target of 4.2pc.&lt;/p&gt;
